-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------ DS18B20 Waterproof Temperature Sensor --------------------------------------------------------------
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Follow instructions here for hardware connection:
https://cityos.io/tutorial/2219/DS18B20-Waterproof-Temperature-Sensor
!!!!!! must have 4.7k ohm pull-up resistor b/t Vcc & Data pins !!!!!!

... and here for the libraries (OneWire & Dallas Temperature Sensor libs):
https://create.arduino.cc/projecthub/iotboys/how-to-use-ds18b20-water-proof-temperature-sensor-2adecc
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------



-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
------------------------------- Compiling/Building --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Compile with arduino-cli:
Example command:
arduino-cli compile --fqbn esp8266:esp8266:nodemcuv2 --build-properties build.extra_flags=-DOSH_NOXMLNS OSH_Sketches/DHT22_Unified_Sensor

... then upload:
Example command:
arduino-cli upload --port /dev/ttyUSB0 --fqbn esp8266:esp8266:nodemcuv2 OSH_Sketches/DHT22_Unified_Sensor
